// November 9th
(1) - fertility is too narrow : 
     => pain to Population : réduction of birth / increase deaths (unified because indistingable ) 
     - show in M5 !  redo,picture 
      Hence : +T implies reduction of potential / plus pain / pain reduces population and efficiency (désengagement, absentéisme. strikes, wars) 

(2) reintroduced savings : voluntary efficiency gains based on investments 
    NOTE: contrary to transition which is set to 100% by default, savings are set to 0% by default  
      - model.cl: 
            c.savingRates : actual rate whose increase trigger investments,
            c.savings = list<Energy>, c.savingFactors[y] : policy (setup by redirection)
            Input (Consumer): maxSaving (for each c, max total gain until 2100), yearlySaving (max yearly increase, set to maxSavings/90) 
            Tactic : savingStart, savingFromPain
      - game.cl:
            getDematerialize(b:Block,y:Year) :  get(b.dematerialize,yearF(y)) + c.savingFactors[y - 1] 
            saves(c,s,y) : sets the new level of savingRate, bookkeeping of saved energy, computes associated investments
            redirection(s,y) : sets the saving ambution (savingFactor) according to the pain level
      - simul.cl: initialize all slots + set yearlySaving
      - display.cl: show in hist(e) and hM2

(3) changed h5+/h5- with multiply% vs improve% (cancel at start is zero)
    added an assertion in simul.cl (init(c))
    h8/h8+ : added India to the modif ! + retune cancellation

